Reprint Requests
All content in the print or online editions is copyrighted by The Emory Wheel and may not be republished or reproduced without permission from the editor-in-chief of The Emory Wheel.
If you would like to reprint content from The Emory Wheel,
please complete and submit this form
to
emorywheelexec@gmail.com
.
Reprint Request Form
by
The Emory Wheel
on Scribd
You will hear back from a representative of the Wheel with permission to reprint without charge or a quote and instructions on how to pay. If you receive permission, you may only reprint content with the following conditions:
• You must reprint the content exactly as it originally appeared in The Emory Wheel (in print or online).
• You must print “Originally appeared in The Emory Wheel, the student newspaper at Emory University. Reprinted with permission.”
• The Emory Wheel retains copyright over all the content. You may not assign or license your reprint rights to anyone without our prior permission.
The minimum charge for a reprinted article is $80, and the minimum charge for a reprinted photo is $40.
The Wheel reserves the right to deny any requests.
